line_1: Where FLORA has with all her roses blush'd;
line_2: The breasts made to be press'd, not to be crush'd —

line_1: When sweet, like modest Worth, she blusht,
line_2: Ye need na doubt, I held my whisht;

line_1: When sweet, like modest Worth, she blusht,
line_2: The infant aith, half-form'd, was crusht;

line_1: When sweet, like modest Worth, she blusht,
line_2: I glowr'd as eerie's I'd been dusht,

line_1: Which richly glowing with carbuncles blushed,
line_2: A lion from the neighbouring forest rushed,

line_1: The Morning ne'r with such a Crimson blusht,
line_2: When from the Arms of sooty Night she rusht.
